<text>There are two forms of respiratory distress syndrome:
* ARDS, which is &quot;acute&quot; (or &quot;adult&quot;) &quot;respiratory distress syndrome&quot;
* Infant respiratory distress syndrome (IRDS), which is a complication of premature birth, also known as hyaline membrane disease (HMD)

Also, respiratory distress can mean:
* Shortness of breath
* Respiratory failure</text><links>
<link wikidata="Q344873" start="56" end="60" title="acute respiratory distress syndrome" label="ARDS"/>
<link wikidata="Q754348" start="156" end="192" title="Infant respiratory distress syndrome" label="Infant respiratory distress syndrome"/>
<link wikidata="Q188008" start="330" end="349" title="Shortness of breath" label="Shortness of breath"/>
